
Natural Language Processing has two sub sections: Natual Language Understanding and Natural Language Generation.

NLU takes up the understanding of the data based on grammar, the context in which it was said and decide on intent and entities.
NLP converts a text into structured data.
NLG generates a text based on structured data.

Major applications of NLG

There are many applications like describing graph nodes based on it's relationships and properties, generate questions, produce reports, etc. For our use case, we will focus on
different methods to generate summary on a visualization dashboard. 

The two below resources talks about NLG in a broad way:

Paper: https://arxiv.org/pdf/1703.09902.pdf
Blog: https://medium.com/sciforce/a-comprehensive-guide-to-natural-language-generation-dd63a4b6e548

